==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek ''mikron'' - "little" and klinein - "to stoop."

===Noun===
'''microcline'''
# {{mineralogy}} A common [[feldspar]] of [[igneous]], [[plutonic]], and [[metamorphic]] [[rock]]s, made of potassium aluminum silicate, (<math>KAlSi_3O_8</math>). Microcline is the main feldspar of [[granite]]. The bluish-green variety is called [[amazonstone]], and is sometimes of gem quality. Used in [[ceramics]], ceramic [[glaze]]s, and as a scouring powder.

